<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Boy, 12, saves drowning man using CPR technique he saw on Stranger Things]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/19/florida-boy-saves-man-cpr-stranger-things]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T09:00:54Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/51b983f7beebcd533d5753795422b06db9290d72/39_0_1243_746 /master/1243.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=6bf6843450aa649ab20ab37e3732bd1e&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;奥斯汀·麦克米伦 (Austen Macmillan) 将其行为登记技术员杰森·皮奎特 (Jason Piquette) 从他家的泳池中拉了出来，然后于 2023 年 9 月救了他的命。该图像是由家庭安全摄像头拍摄的。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;起初，克里斯蒂娜·麦克米伦 (Christina Macmillan) 并不热衷于她 12 岁的儿子奥斯汀 (Austen) 观看&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile .guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/tv-and-radio/stranger-things&quot;>;《怪奇物语》&lt;/a>;，Netflix 虚构节目，讲述一群孩子对抗外星人和恶魔的故事。但在刚刚过去的劳动节，她的儿子使用了他在电视剧中看到的心肺复苏技术来挽救他注册行为技术人员的生命后，她改变了主意。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我对他是否观看这部电影有点犹豫。 ，”麦克米伦告诉卫报，引用了该剧的科幻恐怖前提。 “但我绝对很高兴我让他这么做了。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;奥斯汀·麦克米伦 (Austen Macmillan) 如何营救 30 岁的杰森·皮奎特 (Jason Piquette) 的非凡故事在男孩位于惠灵顿的家中展开，&lt;a href=&quot;x -gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/us-news/florida&quot;>;佛罗里达州&lt;/a>;，9 月 4 日，西棕榈滩附近。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;奥斯汀开始看到大约三年前，皮奎特为 &lt;a href=&quot;https://asatonline.org/for-parents/learn-more-about-special-treatments/applied-behavior-analysis-aba/?gad=1&amp;amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw6p- oBhaYEiwAgg2PgsTb4ISnNmACfWNY3KV2NajfXuZiBVgyl1HIywgz5mrBAIHy8uP6choCfcsQAvD_BwE&quot;>;应用行为分析&lt;/a>;疗法。那天，他们在麦克米伦家庭游泳池里游泳，这是他们每周大约 20 小时在一起工作的一部分。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当他们游泳时，他们最终开始看看谁能在水下屏住呼吸更长时间。 ，用计时器跟踪。当奥斯汀看到皮奎特的一个回合中计时器达到了大约五分钟时，他意识到出了严重的问题。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;3f36f60f1598356f66e252730ce0269622f1a103&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim .co.uk/3f36f60f1598356f66e252730ce0269622f1a103/0_24_604_755/400.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;杰森·皮奎特（左）和奥斯汀·麦克米伦。&quot; width=&quot;400&quot; height=&quot;500&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Jason Piquette（左）和奥斯汀·麦克米伦。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：克里斯蒂娜·麦克米伦提供&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure >; &lt;p>;“我知道那太长了”，奥斯汀后来 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=42&amp;amp;v=Xxm0pzCxAyU&amp;amp;embeds_referring_euri=https%3A%2F%2Fwww .sunnyskyz.com%2F&amp;amp;source_ve_path=MzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMzY4NDIsMjg2NjY&amp;amp;feature=emb_logo&quot;>;告诉&lt;/a>;当地电视新闻台 ABC7。 “他不能那样做。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;麦克米伦家中的监控摄像头记录了奥斯汀游到泳池深处、潜入水池并将皮奎特拉到台阶上的过程。麦克米伦说，奥斯汀试图使用皮奎特手机上的紧急解锁功能拨打紧急求助电话，但他能够呼叫急救人员的触摸屏按钮被破解了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;直到后来，男孩才意识到他可以还通过按住设备侧面的两个按钮几秒钟来激活手机的紧急解锁功能。当时父母不在家的奥斯汀跑到前院尖叫：“来人救命吧！” – 监控摄像头也捕捉到了令人痛苦的时刻。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;奥斯汀很快回到了皮奎特身边，做了他能想到的最有帮助的事情：他开始对皮奎特进行胸部按压。他回忆起与家人一起观看《怪奇物语》的情景，并看到在该剧第一季结局的关键场景中，一个角色如何以这种方式复活另一个角色。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;为此 &lt;a href=&quot;https:// www.youtube.com/watch?v=bsJONXntpig&quot;>;场景&lt;/a>;，由薇诺娜·瑞德 (Winona Ryder) 和大卫·哈伯 (David Harbour) 饰演的角色为她昏迷不醒的儿子（由诺亚·施纳普 (Noah Schnapp) 饰演）进行胸部按压。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;场景以哈伯的角色拼命敲打施纳普角色的胸口而达到高潮，孩子突然复活，喘着气，并被哭泣但如释重负的莱德紧紧拥抱。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在奥斯汀的例子中，经过几分钟的按压和一次胸部撞击（强烈让人想起节目中的那些）后，皮奎特恢复了知觉。几分钟后，奥斯汀的父亲从杂货店回到家，听到儿子惊慌失措的哭声，于是打电话寻求紧急帮助。皮奎特被送往一家医院，医院将他送入重症监护室，在那里他整晚都接受了氧气治疗。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但皮奎特很快就康复出院了，并在同一周五返回工作岗位。麦克米伦说，“一周”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;根据麦克米伦的说法，从那以后的日子里人们产生了一系列的情绪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;其中之一是惊讶。 2016 年的 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.reddit.com/r/StrangerThings/comments/4uy6hq/cpr/&quot;>;Reddit&lt;/a>; 帖子指出了《怪奇物语》第一季结局中如何展示心肺复苏技术在节目设置时还不是标准的。该帖子的一位评论者推测，也许该节目的创作者这样做是因为之前人们根据他们在电影和电视节目中看到的内容进行了挽救生命的心肺复苏术。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;如果确实发生了这种情况”，麦克米伦说，“他们绝对非常聪明。”麦克米伦描述的另一种情感是自豪——因为她儿子的勇气、自信和独立性通过治疗而成长，以至于他拯救了一个成年人的生命。生活。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“他是我的小超级英雄，”麦克米伦告诉《卫报》。 “这表明他比很多人所认为的更有能力，也比他自己所认为的更有能力。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她开玩笑说，她的儿子永远否定了他在试图做事时通常提供的借口。让她相信他根本无法自己打扫房间。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我说，‘伙计，你&lt;em>;可以&lt;/em>;打扫你的房间 - 你可以拉一个成年人-离开房间并进行胸部按压，”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;皮奎特在给《卫报》的一份声明中呼应了麦克米伦的观点。 “奥斯汀在面对令人难以置信的可怕和看似绝望的情况时表现出了勇气，他应该永远知道自己有足够的力量面对生活中的任何事情 - 并且他是英雄。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但是奥斯汀、他的母亲和皮奎特还试图提高人们对心肺复苏术培训和预防相对浅水中&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.shallowwaterblackoutprevention.org/&quot;>;停电&lt;/a>;的认识。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id =&quot;540d3dfc8a20ae4aa9ddfaa2c95b75a65665e9aa&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/540d3dfc8a20ae4aa9ddfaa2c95b75a65665e9aa/12_35_588_736/399.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;奥斯汀麦克米伦于 2023 年 9 月持有美国心脏协会基本生命支持证书。” width=&quot;399&quot; height=&quot;500&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;2023 年 9 月，奥斯汀·麦克米伦 (Austen Macmillan) 手持美国心脏协会基本生命支持证书。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：由克里斯蒂娜·麦克米伦 (Christina Macmillan) 提供&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;麦克米伦表示，9 月 10 日，她安排家人和密友在家中接受心肺复苏术和急救认证课程。课程结束后，奥斯汀拍了一张照片，他自豪地举起他新获得的美国心脏协会基本生命支持证书。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他还花时间学习了解锁手机的所有方法。麦克米伦说，能够拨打紧急电话。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;与此同时，皮奎特在声明中承认，试图在水下屏住呼吸是“一个大错误”。他说，他在尝试的前30秒就昏倒了，怀疑是因为“事先换气过度”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我对危险一无所知，我希望其他人能够从中吸取教训， ”皮奎特说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;皮奎特还表示，他很感激“上帝在奥斯汀最需要的时候给了我力量和智慧来拯救我的生命”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“上帝会继续使用”皮奎特说。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange “ target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https:/ /feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 17:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Elon Musk says Twitter, now X, is to charge all users subscription fees]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/sep/19/elon-musk-twitter-x-subscription-fees-users-posts]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T09:11:11Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/80cf40d05a41227f89a02c078ae255ecdb1cb5ef/0_4_7918_4755 /master/7918.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=d4b80b54a9b071192a8fd861e06e2539&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;埃隆·马斯克在显示 X 标志的电脑屏幕前的照片&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;埃隆·马斯克表示X（以前称为 Twitter）正准备向所有访问该平台的用户收费。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;X 所有者表示，在公司周围建立付费墙将阻止机器人或自动化帐户，这些机器人或自动化帐户已成为特斯拉首席执行官兼世界首富在与以色列总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡会面时表示，X 将向其用户群收费。目前，Twitter 仅向用户收取其订阅服务 X Premium 的费用，该服务提供经过验证的帐户复选标记等福利，iPhone 在美国每月收费 11 美元，在英国每月收费 11 英镑。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span >;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/sep/19/sadiq-khan-says-hundreds-of-thousands-spent-on-anti-ulez- twitter-manipulation&quot;>;萨迪克·汗表示，数十万美元用于反 Ulez Twitter 操纵&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“我们正在转向每月支付少量费用来使用该系统， ”马斯克说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;马斯克表示，机器人的安装成本“只有一小部分”，他补充说，将帐户成本提高到“几美元或其他东西”可能会让软件运营商望而却步。 。他补充道：“此外，每当机器人创建者想要制作另一个机器人时，他们就需要另一种新的支付方式。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;马斯克还表示，X 每月有 5.5 亿用户，每天生成多达 2 亿条帖子。此前，该平台通过不同的方法衡量其用户群，即可货币化的每日活跃用户，在 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2022/oct/28/elon- musk-twitter-hate-speech-concerns-stock-exchange-deal&quot;>;马斯克于 2022 年 10 月收购了该业务&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;随着平台之战，X 所有者提出了付费墙的前景其主要收入来源广告业务的持续下滑。马斯克表示，由于对他对该平台的领导力以及对不当或仇恨内容的管理的担忧，广告商抵制广告，导致广告收入下降了 60%。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;马斯克与内塔尼亚胡的对话被宣传为关于技术和人工智能的讨论，但很快就变成了&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/sep/18/benjamin-netanyahu-elon-musk-antisemitism-twitter-x&quot;>;免费言论和反犹太主义&lt;/a>;，有人指责 X 在解决平台上的种族主义言论方面做得不够。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;内塔尼亚胡表示，他希望马斯克能在第一修正案的范围内找到遏制反犹太主义的方法以及对X的其他形式的仇恨。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我鼓励你并敦促你找到平衡点，”内塔尼亚胡说。 “这是一个艰难的过程。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;马斯克在 X 上使用他的账户表示，他“支持言论自由，但反对任何形式的反犹太主义”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;br>; &lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&quot; /feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br >;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 17:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Germany will suffer worst from world economic slowdown, says OECD]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/sep/19/germany-world-economic-slowdown-oecd-interest-rates-china]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T09:00:53Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/0f03fa7a0a5f04bff7ac5659cc64c49edeef7244/0_276_4500_2700 /master/4500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=9929f5c5b2d5dd377a39f9ffe2798930&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;工人在德国埃森堡的博世家居舒适集团工厂组装热泵。 &lt;/div>;&lt;p>;经济合作与发展组织警告称，由于利率上升和全球贸易疲软导致世界经济放缓，德国预计将遭受最严重的打击。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;这家总部位于巴黎的组织对世界经济做出悲观预测，称欧洲最大的经济体可能是今年除阿根廷外唯一一个在全球经济放缓的背景下出现经济萎缩的 G20 国家。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;经合组织表示，由于能源价格下降和中国放松新冠疫情限制，2023 年开局好于预期，主要国家的经济活动在年底前将放缓，2024 年经济将疲软。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt; span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2023/sep/19/oil-hits-95-per-barrel-politicians-debanked-views-fca -oecd-global-economy-business-live&quot;>;油价触及每桶 95 美元； “没有证据”表明政客因观点而被剥夺银行账户 - 商业直播&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;俄罗斯入侵乌克兰后，提高利率以应对高通胀的影响增加了压力经济合作与发展组织 (OECD) 称，德国重要的贸易伙伴中国的增长低于预期，而欧洲各地的经济活动则疲软。面临着顽固的通货膨胀和&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/sep/14/ecb-raises-interest-rates-inflation&quot;>;较高的利率&lt;/a>;的压力。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;下调中期经济展望中的增长预测，称德国经济今年有望萎缩 0.2%，低于 6 月份的零增长预测。它还对德国 2024 年的经济评级进行了下调，是该报告所涵盖的欧盟国家中降幅最大的，预测增长率为 0.9%，低于之前预测的 1.3%。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;经合组织首席经济学家克莱尔·隆巴德利 (Clare Lombardelli) 表示： “整个欧洲的增长都在放缓，但德国可能是最大的例子。您正在看到通货膨胀对实际收入的影响。这一直在抑制消费者需求。您会看到货币政策紧缩的影响。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“德国可能比其他欧盟经济体更容易受到中国经济放缓的影响。它向中国出口大量商品，进口也很多，所以这是多种因素综合作用的结果。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她表示，经合组织预计任何大型经济体都不会出现衰退，尽管谨慎的经济活动仍将疲软并警告称如果通胀持续居高不下或中国经济活动进一步恶化，预测就会面临风险。家庭和企业仍然面临高利率的压力。 “我们还没有摆脱通货膨胀的困境。现在宣布胜利还为时过早。”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;总体而言，经合组织预计今明两年世界经济增长仍将低于平均水平，2023 年增长 3%，然后放缓至 2%。 2024 年将增长 2.7%。尽管通胀正在消退，但许多经济体仍面临持续的压力，原因是成本压力和某些行业的高公司利润率。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该组织维持对英国 2023 年经济增长的预测不变通胀率为 0.3%，在 G20 国家中排名第三，同时将 2024 年的预期从 1% 下调至 0.8%。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;英国预计将是 G20 国家中通胀率最高的国家，仅次于土耳其和阿根廷，其2023 年的平均利率为 7.2%，之后将下降到接近中间水平，预计 2024 年的利率为 2.9%。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;代表全球 38 个最富裕国家的机构敦促各国央行维持利率不变直到有明显迹象表明潜在的通胀压力正在消退。然而，这将打击企业和消费者信心，从而增加经济增长疲软的风险。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;经济学家预计，全球主要央行即将结束数十年来最激进的加息周期，因为人们越来越担心之前的加息对经济活动的影响。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧洲央行上周&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/sep/14/ecb- raises-interest-rates-inflation&quot;>;将利率提高至 1999 年欧元创立以来的最高水平&lt;/a>;。 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/ lists/tag/business/federal-reserve&quot;>;美联储&lt;/a>;预计周三将维持借贷成本不变，而英国央行则&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business /2023/sep/17/yet-another-bank-of-england-rate-rise-looks-likely-but-this-may-be-the-last&quot;>;可能最后一次加息&lt;/a >; 在周四当前周期的 14 次加息之后。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Lombardelli 表示：“我们看到货币政策正在产生影响。它正在抑制需求——这是应对通胀挑战所必需的——但这意味着我们的增长速度较低。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 17:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Starmer to meet Macron in Paris as thinktank says Labour’s proposed Brexit renegotiation might not be worth it – UK politics live]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/live/2023/sep/19/starmer-macron-paris-labour-brexit-renegotiation-rishi-sunak-uk-politics-latest]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T08:44:10Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5bed21bff05f77bd28d9d5d285a3ca95d7beaf87/649_642_3210_1926 /master/3210.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=ab8ce25fa12195ca20fe0aaee6b79b62&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Keir Starmer 与影子财政大臣 Rachel Reeves 和影子外交大臣 David Lammy 一起抵达巴黎北站.&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 16:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[YouTube suspends Russell Brand’s revenues from his channel]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/sep/19/youtube-suspends-russell-brand-revenues-channel]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T06:54:07Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/01913cf7dc1f2d65f0411ee2528afebab161f4eb/40_0_828_497 /master/828.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=6adc78a08aa01f7b2ce9d1d3278876f6&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Russell Brand 的屏幕截图 &lt;/div>;&lt;p>;YouTube 已暂停 Russell Brand 从其平台频道获得的收入强奸和性侵犯指控对他的财务造成了巨大打击。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这家视频共享和社交媒体网站表示，在对布兰德提出严重指控后，它已暂停了布兰德频道的 YouTube 合作伙伴计划，这意味着他的视频不再能够在该平台上获利。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这位 48 岁的喜剧演员兼演员被指控在 2006 年至 2013 年期间实施强奸、攻击和精神虐待，当时他的名气正处于巅峰期为 BBC、第四频道工作并主演好莱坞电影。他否认了这些指控，称他所有的关系都是双方自愿的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;大都会警方周一表示，他们收到了 2003 年在伦敦市中心苏豪区发生性侵犯的指控。并补充说，目前尚未开展任何调查已启动。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-interactive=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/embed/iframe-wrapper/0.1/boot.js&quot; data-canonical-url=&quot;https://interactive .guim.co.uk/embed/from-tool/generic/index.html?vertical=新闻&amp;amp;opinion-tint=false&amp;amp;title=故事%20tips%3F&amp;amp;description=Do%20you%20have%20information%20about%20this %20story%3F%20Email%20%3Ca%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ab0613%22%20href%3D%22mailto%3Ainvestigations.contact%40theguardian.com%22%3Einvestigations.contact%40theguardian.com%3C%2Fa %3E%2C%20或%20（使用%20a%20非工作%20电话）%20use%20Signal%20or%20%3Ca%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ab0613%22%20href%3D%22https%3A% 2F%2Fapi.whatsapp.com%2Fsend%3Fphone%3D447721857348%22%3EWhatsApp%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20message%20%2B44%207721%20857%20348.%20For%20the%20most%20secure%20communications%2C %20use%20%3Ca%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ab0613%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fsecuredrop%22%3ESecureDrop%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20see %20%3Ca%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ab0613%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fhelp%2Fng-interactive%2F2017%2Fmar%2F17%2F联系监护人-securely%22%3Eour%20guide%3C%2Fa%3E.&amp;amp;link=false&quot; data-alt=&quot;故事提示嵌入&quot;>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/embed/ from-tool/generic/index.html?vertical=新闻&amp;opinion-tint=false&amp;title=Story%20tips%3F&amp;description=Do%20you%20have%20information%20about%20this%20story%3F%20Email%20% 3Ca%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ab0613%22%20href%3D%22mailto%3Ainvestigations.contact%40theguardian.com%22%3Einvestigations.contact%40theguardian.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20(使用%20a%20非工作%20电话)%20use%20Signal%20or%20%3Ca%20style%3D%22color%3A%23ab0613%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fapi.whatsapp.com%2Fsend %3Fphone%3D447721857348%22%3EWhatsApp%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20message%20%2B44%207721%20857%20348.%20For%20the%20most%20secure%20communications%2C%20use%20%3Ca%20style% 3D%22color%3A%23ab0613%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fsecuredrop%22%3ESecureDrop%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20see%20%3Ca%20style%3D% 22color%3A%23ab0613%22%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fhelp%2Fng-interactive%2F2017%2Fmar%2F17%2F安全地联系监护人%22%3Eour%20guide% 3C%2Fa%3E.&amp;amp;link=false&quot;>;互动&lt;/a>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;YouTube 发言人表示：“我们已暂停 Russell Brand 频道的盈利，因为该频道违反了我们的&lt;a href=&quot;https: //support.google.com/youtube/answer/7650329?hl=zh-CN&quot;>;创作者责任政策&lt;/a>;。如果创作者的平台外行为损害了我们的用户、员工或生态系统，我们会采取行动保护社区。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;行业专家对品牌进行了评估&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com /culture/2023/sep/18/how-russell-brand-maintains-his-venue-and-influence?CMP=Share_iOSApp_Other&quot;>;每个视频可能赚取 2,000 到 4,000 英镑&lt;/a>;，根据每周五个视频，每年可产生近 100 万英镑的收入。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;YouTube 的&lt;a href=&quot;https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/7650329?hl=en&quot;>;创作者责任指南&lt;/a>;指出，“如果创作者的平台外行为损害了用户、员工或生态系统，平台可以采取行动保护我们的社区，包括暂停获利。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“当创作者暂停 YouTube 合作伙伴计划后，他们不得使用新的或替代频道来规避我们的执法决定。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 15:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Oil hits $95 per barrel; ‘no evidence’ of politicians being debanked over views – business live]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2023/sep/19/oil-hits-95-per-barrel-politicians-debanked-views-fca-oecd-global-economy-business-live]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T06:46:09Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/d45723d9303a80c7c234f5797140064513a51370/0_104_5472_3283 /master/5472.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=6e181601c53b37292ae1458be54f525a&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;位于里海的 Neft Daslari 石油钻井平台和工业定居点，距离阿塞拜疆巴库约 100 公里。&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 14:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Tigray atrocities continuing almost a year after ceasefire, UN experts warn]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/sep/19/tigray-ethiopia-atrocities-continuing-after-ceasefire-un-rights-experts-warn]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T05:30:49Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/91ac8170974a40df832437f84de6107872c7b643/0_205_3500_2100 /master/3500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=6c681476ada3599e3d43a9507d59f5ce&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;难民营里的小孩子看着镜头，而年长的年轻人站在背景中&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;据联合国专家小组称，在停火正式结束血腥内战十多个月后，埃塞俄比亚北部提格雷地区的侵犯人权行为仍在发生。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;联合国的最新报告 &lt;a href =&quot;https://www.ohchr.org/en/hr-bodies/hrc/ichre-ethiopa/index&quot;>;埃塞俄比亚国际人权专家委员会&lt;/a>;表示，该国政府未能保护其公民免受与埃塞俄比亚联邦军队并肩作战的民兵和厄立特里亚军队犯下了“严重且持续的”侵犯人权行为&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/07/people- are-under-siege-why-ethiopias-war-in-tigray-isnt-over&quot;>;留在提格雷边境地区&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这些侵犯人权行为包括性暴力和基于性别的暴力根据&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ohchr.org/sites/default/files/documents/hrbodies/hrcouncil/chreetiopia/A_HRC_54_55_AUV.pdf&quot;>;报告&lt;/ a>;，周一发布。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;报告称，埃塞俄比亚政府发起的“过渡时期司法”进程不符合国际标准，并对埃塞俄比亚人口最多的两个地区奥罗米亚州和阿姆哈拉州最近暴力事件的增加表示震惊专家们表示，未能实施有意义的司法程序正在助长有罪不罚的文化，并增加了未来发生暴行的风险。他们指出，埃塞俄比亚针对种族和政治团体以及 LGBT 的网络仇恨言论不断增加报告称：“提格雷冲突仍未以任何全面和平方式得到解决，继续造成苦难。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“同样令人担忧的是，埃塞俄比亚的敌对行动目前已达到了令人震惊的地步。全国范围内发生了严重的侵犯行为，特别是在阿姆哈拉地区，但在奥罗米亚州和其他地方也正在发生。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“国家面临的风险以及东部地区的稳定和人权的享受非洲，无论怎么强调都不过分。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;提格雷冲突于 2020 年 11 月爆发，并蔓延到埃塞俄比亚其他地区，是近年来最血腥的冲突之一。据信该事件已造成数十万人死亡，其特点是屠杀和强奸。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian .com/global-development/2023/aug/07/people-are-under-siege-why-ethiopias-war-in-tigray-isnt-over&quot;>;“人们被围困”：为什么埃塞俄比亚的提格雷战争不是“ &lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;提格雷 600 万人口中，约有 540 万仍然依赖人道主义援助，尽管自 3 月中旬以来，对饱受战争蹂躏的地区的粮食援助已暂停。官员揭露了一个&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/jun/29/ethiopia-hunger-food-aid-suspended-usaid-wfp&quot;>;官员的大规模全国性计划窃取捐赠的粮食&lt;/a>;。自6月以来，对埃塞俄比亚全境的粮食援助已被搁置。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;联合国人权机构此前的一份报告发现，各方在战争期间都犯下了侵权行为，其中许多行为构成战争罪。它还得出结论，政府利用饥饿作为武器。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;埃塞俄比亚政府发言人没有回应对最新报告发表评论的请求。埃塞俄比亚官员此前曾谴责联合国委员会具有政治动机，阻止其调查人员并试图取消其资金。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该委员会的任期将于 12 月到期。目前尚不清楚联合国人权理事会是否会在本届会议期间将其延期一年，本届会议将持续到10月6日。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;美国和欧盟在会议期间暂停了对埃塞俄比亚价值数亿美元的援助。战争，并以侵犯人权为由。他们表示，追究这些罪行的责任是恢复这种支持和关系正常化的先决条件。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;美国还&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2021/may/23/华盛顿加强立场，打击埃塞俄比亚的暴行&quot;>;对参与侵权行为的个人实施制裁&lt;/a>;，总统乔·拜登本月重申了这一制裁措施。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但是，有人们担心欧盟官员可能会放弃追究责任的要求，并且不再呼吁延长联合国人权委员会的任期。在乌克兰战争重新引发俄罗斯与西方之间对非洲影响力的争夺之后，欧盟渴望加强与埃塞俄比亚的外交关系。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 14:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Symbol of hope’: Lahaina’s beloved banyan shows new growth after fires]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/18/lahaina-banyan-tree-hawaii-wildfires-new-growth]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T05:00:49Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/aa172dce661a7d4b0451e892693347217c9ab1c2/0_0_6000_4000 /master/6000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=b120b88c3641eb8fef03f1031a2f0d86&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;拉海纳镇中心的一棵 150 年树龄的榕树在去年被烧焦后出现了新的生长迹象&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;拉海纳镇中心一棵巨大的、受人喜爱的、已有 150 年历史的榕树，上个月致命的野火肆虐夏威夷毛伊岛时被烧焦，现在却显示出新生长的绿色迹象。&lt; /p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/15/hawaii-fires-death-toll -update-dna-testing-missing&quot;>;夏威夷火灾：DNA 测试有助于识别受害者，死亡人数降至 97 人&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;这棵树被描述为“ &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/lahaina-banyan-tree-burned-hawaii-wildfire&quot;>;拉海纳镇的心跳&lt;/a>;”被严重烧焦，但在上个月的大火造成至少 97 人死亡并将这座历史名镇的大部分地区化为灰烬之后，它仍然屹立不倒。 guim.co.uk/918d30c06cb80ffe84e72f583fe9efe02ed38f27/0_0_4200_2800/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;2023 年 8 月 11 日，一名男子坐在因野火受损的历史悠久的榕树上。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;667&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;这棵猛犸树是印度传教士的礼物，于 1873 年种植。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Rick Bowmer/AP&lt;/span>; &lt;/根据夏威夷土地和自然资源部 (DLNR) 的说法，从那时起，树艺师就自愿投入时间和专业知识来拯救这棵树，并建议从这棵树烧焦的树枝上长出新叶子。复苏的积极迹象。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“对我来说，这是希望的象征。我们牢记在心，努力让这棵树回归，给拉海纳带来一些希望。”景观承包商 Chris Imonti &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.hawaiimagazine.com/a-ray-of-hope- the-lahaina-banyan-tree/&quot;>;告诉&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.hawaiinewsnow.com/2023/08/31/3-weeks-after-lahaina-wildfire-towns-famed-本月早些时候，banyan-tree-sees-hopeful-signs-life/&quot;>;记者&lt;/a>;看到他和其他人小心翼翼地为树周围的土壤通气并补充养分。 “我们不知道接下来会发生什么，但我认为这对每个人来说都将是一个新的开始。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://vimeo.com/864251878&quot;>; &lt; iframe height=&quot;960&quot; width=&quot;1920&quot; src=&quot;https://player.vimeo.com/video/864251878?app_id=122963&amp;amp;dnt=true&amp;amp;dnt=true&quot;frameborder=&quot;0&quot;allowfullscreen>;&lt;/iframe >; &lt;figcaption>; 志愿者已经在树的根部浇了数千加仑的水，并正在采集根部样本来测量树的健康状况。 &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Imoti 和其他志愿者在树根上浇了数千加仑的水，并正在采集根部样本来测量树的健康状况。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这棵猛犸树是一棵印度传教士的礼物。它于 1873 年种植，比夏威夷群岛被宣布为美国领土早了四分之一个世纪。对于几代人来说，它一直是一个珍贵的地标，为社区活动和庆祝活动提供遮蔽。在火灾发生之前，该镇庆祝了榕树的&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mauinews.com/news/local-news/2023/04/birthday-party-to-mark-iconic-lahaina-banyan-trees -150周年/&quot;>;150岁生日&lt;/a>;与蛋糕。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;现在，城镇的大部分地区已被大火夷为平地，数千名流离失所的居民一直住在酒店和度假屋里。 Rental assistance will be offered for 18 months, officials said, and the road to rebuilding the town will likely be long.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;47831e24c8d26b0f4c86676afb070f6eacd3ef0e&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/47831e24c8d26b0f4c86676afb070f6eacd3ef0e/0_0_5184_3456/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;The banyan tree before the Maui wildfires.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;667&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;The banyan tree before the Maui wildfires.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: robertharding/Alamy&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Last week, the US energy secretary Jennifer Granholm toured the wreckage in Lahaina, where teams are still searching for missing persons.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Lāhainā&#39;s Banyan tree represents the deep roots of this community. Even in the face of unspeakable heartache, its limbs reach outward and upward,” she wrote on social media. “Honored to bear witness as the people of Maui rebuild, recover, and reach outward and upward themselves.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 13:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Australia now in El Niño climate pattern, increasing bushfire risk, BOM says]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/sep/19/australia-el-nino-declaration-bom-bushfire-risk-summer-weather-temperature]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T05:01:20Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/28c7f424acc70f071f90694cc61647b57b4207d2/0_173_5184_3110/master/5184.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=d942dd8e6c4e84e52a3ce60040732436&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Australia is now in the grip of an El Niño climate pattern&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;The Bureau of Meteorology has declared that Australia is now in an El Niño climate pattern that will increase the chances of a hot and dry summer, and heighten the risk of dangerous bushfires.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The announcement comes amid &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/sep/19/nsw-schools-closed-heatwave-australia-high-fire-danger-total-fire-bans&quot;>;soaring temperatures and extreme fire danger&lt;/a>; across parts of south-east Australia. Total fire bans were declared for the New South Wales south coast and greater Sydney region on Tuesday, while &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/sep/17/residents-of-queensland-towns-emerald-and-beerwah-told-to-evacuate-as-bushfire-approaches&quot;>;bushfire evacuation orders&lt;/a>; were issued in parts of Queensland during the week.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The UN&#39;s weather agency, the World Meteorological Organization (WMO), &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/jul/04/climate-heating-el-nino-has-arrived-and-threatens-lives-declares-un&quot;>;declared the onset of an El Niño&lt;/a>; in July, after the US National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) did so in June.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/jul/09/el-nino-what-does-it-mean-for-australia-and-are-more-heatwaves-and-bushfires-inevitable&quot;>;El Niño: what does it mean for Australia – and are more heatwaves and bushfires inevitable?&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;The BoM has had Australia on an El Niño alert since May, saying there was a 70% chance of the system locking in place by the summer.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But until Tuesday, Australia&#39;s weather agency had stopped short of making the declaration, pointing to a lack of tell-tale signs in the atmosphere.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;El Niños are characterised by warmer than average sea surface temperatures in a central region of the equatorial Pacific. Those temperatures have been enough to see WMO and NOAA declare the climate pattern in place.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But the BoM had said the atmosphere was not reacting to the hotter temperatures. In an El Niño, the trade winds that blow from east to west over the Pacific weaken or even reverse.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/jul/09/el-nino-what-does-it-mean-for-australia-and-are-more-heatwaves-and-bushfires-inevitable&quot;>;Climate and bushfire experts have said&lt;/a>; that the drier and hotter conditions associated with El Niño will raise the risk of dangerous bushfires.&lt;/p>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/email-newsletters?CMP=copyembed&quot;>;Sign up for Guardian Australia&#39;s free morning and afternoon email newsletters for your daily news roundup&lt;/a>;&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;p>;El Niño tends to result in hotter than average temperatures across most of southern Australia. For eastern Australia, nine of the 10 driest winter-spring periods on record have occurred during El Niño years.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The BoM has also confirmed that a positive Indian Ocean dipole (IOD) event is underway. The IOD is determined by differences in sea surface temperature between the eastern and western Indian Ocean.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A positive IOD usually results in decreased spring rainfall for central and south-east Australia. The climate phenomenon usually begins in late autumn or winter.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;According to the Bureau, the risk of a significant fire danger season in south-east Australia is significantly higher after an El Niño year, particularly when combined with a positive IOD.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The previous three Australian summers have seen a triple La Niña – the cooler and wetter phase of the El Niño-Southern Oscillation.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Those conditions have encouraged large amounts of grass and vegetation to grow that could become fuel for fires.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Australasian Fire Authorities Council &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/aug/23/australian-bushfire-season-how-to-prepare&quot;>;has issued an outlook for spring&lt;/a>; showing increased risk of bushfires over large parts of Queensland and NSW and parts of Victoria and the Northern Territory.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 13:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Mutilating the tree of life’: Wildlife loss accelerating, scientists warn]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/sep/19/mutilating-the-tree-of-life-wildlife-loss-accelerating-scientists-warn]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T05:00:49Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/15faab629b41725b19e09045034fae75ff070e1a/184_161_5070_3044/master/5070.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=37e3a35e243640577debcaabbdeb8f34&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Northern muriqui in a tree&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Groups of animal species are vanishing at a rate 35 times higher than average due to human activity, according to researchers, who say it is further evidence that a sixth mass extinction in Earth&#39;s history is under way and accelerating.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Scientists analysing the rate at which closely related animal species have gone extinct in the past 500 years have found they would have taken 18,000 years to vanish in the absence of humans, and the rate at which they are being lost is increasing.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pnas.org/cgi/doi/10.1073/pnas.2306987120&quot;>;study&lt;/a>;, published in the journal Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, found that at least 73 mammal, bird, reptile and amphibian species groupings have gone extinct since 1500. If trends had followed the average pre-human impact rates of extinction, just two would have been expected to disappear, they estimated. Those lost include the elephant birds of Madagascar, moa from New Zealand and Hawaiian moho honeyeaters.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Due to habitat destruction, the climate crisis and the illegal trade in wildlife, losses are projected to accelerate in the coming years. In the worst-case scenario – that all currently endangered species groups disappear by the end of the century – the rate would be 354 times above the average for the past million years.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The new research focuses on “genera”, the plural of “genus”. Groups of species are known as a genus, the taxonomic classification above species. For example, horses and zebras are in the same genus, as are dogs, wolves and coyotes. The authors expected genera to have a lower rate of extinction than individual species. They found them to be similar.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Previous research on fossil records has estimated that before the impact of humans, nearly one in 10,000 genera would disappear every century. As there are about 5,400 known vertebrate genera, excluding fishes, one genus would be expected to become extinct every 250 years if those rates held, according to the paper.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The authors, Prof Gerardo Ceballos and Prof Paul Ehrlich, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2015/jun/19/humans-creating-sixth-great-extinction-of-animal-species-say-scientists&quot;>;have previously found that species are becoming extinct on a scale&lt;/a>; akin to the event that wiped out the dinosaurs, and warn that the loss is a threat to the persistence of human civilisation.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;While the claim that a sixth mass extinction is under way is disputed by some scientists, a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ipbes.net/global-assessment&quot;>;2019 UN assessment&lt;/a>; of the health of the planet found 1 million species were at risk of vanishing due to human pressures on the environment.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;c992af3ea965032c749fb8fa01ea521fe6062c51&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/c992af3ea965032c749fb8fa01ea521fe6062c51/0_0_1435_798/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;A vaquita porpoise, a critically endangered species in the Pacific Ocean near Mexico.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;556&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;A vaquita porpoise, a critically endangered species in the Pacific Ocean near Mexico.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Paula Olson/AP&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;“Such mutilation of the tree of life and the resulting loss of ecosystem services provided by biodiversity to humanity is a serious threat to the stability of civilisation. Immediate political, economic and social efforts of an unprecedented scale are essential if we are to prevent these extinctions and their societal impacts,” the study found.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Prof Ceballos, of the Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México, who led the research, told the Guardian that the results were worse than he expected, but said there was still time to act.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“By losing all these genera, we are losing the foundations of the planet to have life in general and human life in particular. If you have a wall made of bricks, if you lose some, it won&#39;t collapse but it won&#39;t be as strong. If you lose many bricks, eventually it will collapse. The combination of the gases in the atmosphere that allows us to have life on the planet depends on plants, animals and organisms. People say that we are alarmist by saying that we expect a collapse. We are alarmist because we are alarmed,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“As dramatic as the results are, what is important to mention is that we still have time. The window of opportunity is closing rapidly. There is hope but we need to act quickly,” he added.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/01/wolves-declared-extinct-in-andalucia-spain-aoe&quot;>;&#39;Shameful loss&#39;: wolves declared extinct in Andalucía&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Ben Garrod, a professor of evolutionary biology and science engagement at the University of East Anglia, who was not a co-author, said the study was a stark warning.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“The very framework to which all nature – including our own species – adheres is in serious jeopardy. With extinction rates from a whole range of species and species groups being so much higher than we&#39;d typically expect, it&#39;s hard to see why global governments, leading businesses and the general public are not doing everything possible to mitigate this devastating loss,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Extinction is irreversible,” he added. “From a more human-centric perspective, it&#39;s almost impossible to predict which of these losses will have a significant impact on our own species. It&#39;s an existential gamble we should think very hard about before taking.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Find more &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://front/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/fronts/environment/series/the-age-of-extinction&quot;>;age of extinction coverage here&lt;/a>;, and follow biodiversity reporters &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/phoeb0?lang=en&quot;>;Phoebe Weston&lt;/a>; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/pgreenfielduk?lang=en&quot;>;Patrick Greenfield&lt;/a>; on &lt;/em>;&lt;em>;X for all the latest news and features&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 13:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia-Ukraine war live: ‘major’ fire at Lviv warehouse after attack, Ukraine says; Zelenskiy questions Russia’s place at UN]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/sep/19/russia-ukraine-war-live-updates-major-fire-lviv-warehouse-attack-zelenskiy-questions-russias-place-at-un]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-19T04:51:37Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ef2d930643a1903d8192b29c04a643e70ea2c50f/0_0_5428_3257 /master/5428.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=db87648bbe8ac59282ce5dfe4b1a2fe7&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Volodymyr Zelenskiy（左）在纽约一家医院与受伤的乌克兰士兵在一起。&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 19 Sep 2023 12:52:01 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>